So let's first simplify the given expression $\frac{z_3 - z_1}{z_2 - z_1} \cdot \frac{z - z_2}{z - z_3}.$
Let $z = a + bi$, where $a$ and $b$ are real numbers. Then
\begin{align*}
\frac{z_3 - z_1}{z_2 - z_1} \cdot \frac{z - z_2}{z - z_3} &= \frac{(78 + 99i) - (18 + 83i)}{(18 + 39i) - (18 + 83i)} \cdot \frac{(a + bi) - (18 + 39i)}{(a + bi) - (78 + 99i)} \\
&= \frac{60 + 16i}{-44i} \cdot \frac{(a - 18) + (b - 39)i}{(a - 78) + (b - 99)i}.
\end{align*}
Multiplying the numerators and denominators, we get
\begin{align*}
\frac{60 + 16i}{-44i} \cdot \frac{(a - 18) + (b - 39)i}{(a - 78) + (b - 99)i} &= \frac{(60 + 16i)(a - 18) + (60 + 16i)(b - 39)i}{-44i((a - 78) + (b - 99)i)} \\
&= \frac{(60a - 1080 + 16ai - 288) + (60b - 2340i + 16bi - 624)i}{-44i(a - 78) + 44b - 4360}
\end{align*}
This simplifies to
\begin{align*}
\frac{-1116 + 16ai + 60b}{-44a + 44(b - 99)i + 4360} &= \frac{60b - 1116 + (16a + 60)i}{4360 - 44a - 44bi + 4360} \\
&= \frac{60b - 1116 + (16a + 60)i}{8720 - 44(a + b - 100)i}.
\end{align*}
Now, for this expression to be real, the imaginary part of the numerator must equal the imaginary part of the denominator times some real number. Thus, we must have 
\begin{align*}
\frac{16a + 60}{b - 18 - 100a + 1100b - 28000} &= 0.
\end{align*}
Solving for $a$ and $b$, we get $a = 8$ and $b = 1100b - 28000$. Since the problem states that $b$ is the greatest possible, we have $b = 1100 \cdot 11 - 2800 = 820$. Thus, the real part of $z$ is $\boxed{8}$. </answer>

solution:
In the coordinate plane, let $A = (0,1),$ $B = (1,-1),$ and $P = (x,x).$  Then
\[AP = \sqrt{x^2 + (1 - x)^2}\]and
\[BP = \sqrt{(x - 1)^2 + (x + 1)^2},\]so we want to minimize $AP + BP,$ subject to $P$ lying on the line $y = x.$

[asy]
unitsize(2.5 cm);

pair A, B, P;

A = (0,1);
B = (1,-1);
P = (0.8,0.8);

draw(A--P--B);
draw((-0.2,-0.2)--(1.2,1.2),dashed);

label("$y = x$", (1.2,1.2), NE);

dot("$A$", A, NW);
dot("$B$", B, SE);
dot("$P$", P, N);
[/asy]

By the Triangle Inequality, $AP + BP \ge AB = \sqrt{5}.$  Equality occurs when $P$ is the intersection of the line $y = x$ and line $AB$ (which occurs when $x = \frac{1}{3}$), so the minimum value is $\boxed{\sqrt{5}}.$

